
[1]chrisom

   CHRISOM, n. [See Chrism.] a child that dies within a month after its
   birth; so called from the chrisom-cloth, a linen cloth anointed with
   holy oil, which was formerly laid over a childs face when it was
   baptized. Also, the cloth itself.
